quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  27,77,and it is a guidance and mercy for the believers
  27,78,"Indeed your Lord will decide between them by His judgement. He is All-Mighty, All-Knowing"
  27,79,So put your trust in Allah for you are on the manifest truth
  27,80,"Surely you cannot make the dead hear you, nor can you make the deaf hear your call if they turn back in flight"
  27,81,"nor can you direct the blind to the Right Way, preventing them from falling into error. You can make only those who believe in Our verses to hear the call and then submit"
  27,82,"And when the time for the fulfilment of Our Word against them will come, We shall bring forth for them a beast from the earth who will speak to them because people did not believe in Our Signs"
  27,83,"Just imagine the Day when We shall muster from every nation a large group of those who gave the lie to Our Signs, and they shall be duly arranged in ranks"
  27,84,"until, when all of them have arrived, Allah will say: \"Did you give the lie to My Signs even without encompassing them with your knowledge? If that is not so, what did you do"
  27,85,"And the Word will come to pass against them because of their wrong-doing: they will then be able to utter nothing"
  27,86,Did they not perceive that We had made the night so that they may repose in it and made the day clear and shining. Surely there are Signs in this for those who believe
  27,87,The Day when the Trumpet will be blown all those who are in the heavens and on the earth shall be terror stricken - all except those whom Allah wills - and everyone shall come to Him utterly abject
  27,88,"You now see the mountains and consider them firmly fixed, but then they shall pass away even as clouds pass away. That will be the handiwork of Allah Who has created everything with perfect wisdom. He is well aware of what you do"